abstract: Senator Bernie Sanders of Vermont climbed to a narrow lead in a new Monmouth poll of New Hampshire voters, who will cast their ballots on Tuesday.
lead_paragraph: Senator Bernie Sanders of Vermont climbed to a narrow lead in a new Monmouth poll of New Hampshire voters, who will cast their ballots on Tuesday.
headline_main: Sanders leads Monmouth poll of New Hampshire voters.

abstract: And Michael Bloomberg and Bernie Sanders are competing fiercely in places like Fresno, where candidates very rarely go.
snippet: And Michael Bloomberg and Bernie Sanders are competing fiercely in places like Fresno, where candidates very rarely go.
lead_paragraph: FRESNO, Calif. — “There’s nothing magical about California,” Michael R. Bloomberg declared after a day flying through the state — or Iowa, for that matter, he added.

abstract: Tom Steyer spent nearly $17 million on television ads in Iowa but emerged from the caucuses with less than 1 percent of the state delegate count. What happened?
lead_paragraph: Tom Steyer spent nearly $17 million on television ads in Iowa but emerged from the caucuses with less than 1 percent of the state delegate count. What happened?
headline_main: Tom Steyer, who barely registered in Iowa, attacks Buttigieg.

abstract: MANCHESTER, N.H. — For over a year, the airwaves in Iowa were inundated by $70 million of political ads, as most of the top-tier campaigns went all-in on the first caucus state with substantially less attention paid to New Hampshire.
lead_paragraph: MANCHESTER, N.H. — For over a year, the airwaves in Iowa were inundated by $70 million of political ads, as most of the top-tier campaigns went all-in on the first caucus state with substantially less attention paid to New Hampshire.

abstract: The tensions surrounding the Democratic presidential race bubbled up at the South Carolina State House today after a state senator suggested that one of his colleagues had sold out to Tom Steyer, the hedge fund billionaire.
lead_paragraph: The tensions surrounding the Democratic presidential race bubbled up at the South Carolina State House today after a state senator suggested that one of his colleagues had sold out to Tom Steyer, the hedge fund billionaire.
headline_main: Tensions boil over in South Carolina over reported Steyer payments.

abstract: They said what was, essentially, the only thing they could say: “Voters, please do what the Senate didn’t.”
snippet: They said what was, essentially, the only thing they could say: “Voters, please do what the Senate didn’t.”
lead_paragraph: The Democratic presidential candidates have been responding this afternoon to the thing they all knew was coming: the Senate’s acquittal of President Trump. And they all said what was, essentially, the only thing they could say: “Voters, please do what the Senate didn’t.”

abstract: Black lawmakers in South Carolina are calling on former Vice President Joe Biden to disavow statements from a longtime friend and campaign surrogate that they say are racist.
snippet: Black lawmakers in South Carolina are calling on former Vice President Joe Biden to disavow statements from a longtime friend and campaign surrogate that they say are racist.
lead_paragraph: COLUMBIA, S.C. — Black lawmakers in South Carolina are calling on former Vice President Joe Biden to disavow statements from a longtime friend and campaign surrogate that they say are racist.
headline_main: Black Lawmakers Demand Biden Disavow Surrogate's Comments
headline_print_headline: Black Lawmakers Demand Biden Disavow Surrogate's Comments

abstract: MANCHESTER, N.H. — The presidential campaign of Tom Steyer paid the chairman of the South Carolina Legislative Black Caucus more than $42,000 in a little more than a month to serve as a senior adviser to the campaign, nearly triple what his campaign manager earns per month, according to campaign finance records.
lead_paragraph: MANCHESTER, N.H. — The presidential campaign of Tom Steyer paid the chairman of the South Carolina Legislative Black Caucus more than $42,000 in a little more than a month to serve as a senior adviser to the campaign, nearly triple what his campaign manager earns per month, according to campaign finance records.
